    <summaries>
      <summary>
        <versionCode>00</versionCode>
        <actionDate>2018-05-09</actionDate>
        <actionDesc>Introduced in House</actionDesc>
        <updateDate>2018-05-30T21:03:05Z</updateDate>
        <text><![CDATA[ <p><b>Expanding Oversight of Opioid Prescribing and Payment Act of 2018</b></p> <p>This bill requires the Medicare Payment Advisory Commission to report to Congress on:&nbsp;(1) how Medicare pays for opioid and non-opioid pain management treatments in inpatient and outpatient hospital settings; (2) current incentives for prescribing opioid and non-opioid treatments under Medicare inpatient and outpatient prospective payment systems, along with recommendations to address any identified adverse incentives; and (3) how opioid use is currently tracked and monitored through Medicare and any areas for improvement.</p>]]></text>
      </summary>
      <summary>
        <versionCode>36</versionCode>
        <actionDate>2018-06-19</actionDate>
        <actionDesc>Passed House amended</actionDesc>
        <updateDate>2018-07-20T16:33:24Z</updateDate>
        <text><![CDATA[ <p><b>Expanding Oversight of Opioid Prescribing and Payment Act of 2018</b></p> <p>(Sec. 2) This bill requires the Medicare Payment Advisory Commission to report to Congress on:&nbsp;(1) how Medicare pays for opioid and non-opioid pain management treatments in inpatient and outpatient hospital settings; (2) current incentives for prescribing opioid and non-opioid treatments under Medicare inpatient and outpatient prospective payment systems, along with recommendations to address any identified adverse incentives; and (3) how opioid use is currently tracked and monitored through Medicare and any areas for improvement.</p> ]]></text>
      </summary>
